00d7 is an accrual red flag.","why_it_can_fail":"One-off working-capital swings or a capex year can distort a single ratio; the 5-yr median smooths it."},{"label":"Balance-sheet safety","value":0.0,"unit":"\u00d7 D/E","status":"good","read":"Conservatively financed (D/E 0.00\u00d7, interest cover 71.8\u00d7).","meaning":"Latest debt-to-equity and interest coverage (EBIT \u00f7 interest) from the balance sheet.","why_useful":"Low debt and high interest cover let a business survive a downturn; high debt amplifies trouble.","why_it_can_fail":"Off-balance-sheet leases/guarantees aren't captured; a cash-rich firm can show low D/E yet still be risky elsewhere."},{"label":"Earnings momentum","value":10.04,"unit":"% YoY","status":"ok","read":"Profit up 10% YoY \u2014 modest.","meaning":"Trailing-twelve-month net profit vs the year-ago TTM (and whether the YoY rate is rising = 'accelerating').","why_useful":"Improving, accelerating earnings tend to drive re-rating; falling profit warns of a deteriorating business.","why_it_can_fail":"TTM can be lumpy for cyclicals/one-offs; cross-check the multi-year trend on the Fundamentals tab."}]},"valuation":{"ok":true,"is_bank":false,"pe_now":11.9,"pe_percentile":36.0,"median_pe":15.2,"earnings_yield_pct":8.4,"pb":3.2,"ev_ebitda":8.72,"quality_score":58.0,"pat_cagr_5y_pct":34.9,"peg":0.34,"cheapness":{"status":"ok","read":"P/E at the 36-percentile of its 10-yr range \u2014 mid-range vs its own history."},"expectations":"At 11.9\u00d7 earnings for ~35% 5-yr profit CAGR, the market is paying \u22480.34\u00d7 growth (PEG). >2 = a lot already priced in; <1 = cheap if growth holds.","cyclical_caveat":null,"meaning":"P/E percentile = where today's price-to-earnings sits within the stock's own last-10-yr range (low = cheap vs its past). Paired with the Quality score and 5-yr profit growth so a cheap multiple is judged against business strength, not in isolation.","why_useful":"Cheapness only matters relative to quality and growth \u2014 a low P/E on a declining or peak-cyclical business is a trap, not a bargain.","why_it_can_fail":"P/E breaks for loss-makers / one-offs; for banks use P/B not EV/EBITDA; a multiple cheap vs history can stay cheap if the business has structurally de-rated."},"ownership":{"ok":true,"na":null,"holders":{"Promoter":{"periods":["Jun 2023","Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[51.28,51.28,51.28,51.28,51.28,51.28,51.28,51.28,51.28,51.28,51.28,51.28],"latest_pct":51.28,"chg_1y_pp":0.0},"FII":{"periods":["Jun 2023","Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[14.95,13.68,11.56,8.99,10.43,12.08,14.13,15.81,15.06,16.22,19.67,22.27],"latest_pct":22.27,"chg_1y_pp":6.46},"DII":{"periods":["Jun 2023","Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[15.38,17.47,18.8,18.82,19.12,19.29,17.99,15.7,15.76,15.45,12.35,10.75],"latest_pct":10.75,"chg_1y_pp":-4.95},"Public":{"periods":["Jun 2023","Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[18.4,17.57,18.38,20.93,19.16,17.34,16.6,17.21,17.9,17.05,16.7,15.69],"latest_pct":15.69,"chg_1y_pp":-1.52}},"pledge":null,"events":[{"date":"23-Feb-2024","subject":"Interim Dividend - Rs  2 Per Share","materiality":"Low"},{"date":"20-Sep-2024","subject":"Annual General Meeting/Dividend - Rs 2 Per Share","materiality":"Low"},{"date":"29-Nov-2024","subject":"Interim Dividend - Rs 4 Per Share","materiality":"Low"},{"date":"14-Feb-2025","subject":"Interim Dividend - Rs 4 Per Share","materiality":"Low"},{"date":"19-Sep-2025","subject":"Dividend - Rs 2.50 Per Share","materiality":"Low"},{"date":"14-Nov-2025","subject":"Interim Dividend - Rs 4 Per Share","materiality":"Low"},{"date":"06-Feb-2026","subject":"Interim Dividen